[SN]TITLE[SN]
Stotfold GP Dr Robert Lewis denies indecent assaults

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A GP from Bedfordshire has denied nearly 40 indecent assaults against 24 female patients.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Dr Robert Lewis, 49, of Shefford, pleaded not guilty at Luton Crown Court to 20 allegations after earlier denying a further 17 charges.
The first allegations made relate to pre-employment medicals he carried out between 1999 and 2003. He has been suspended from practising as a doctor.
A trial is due to take place in October.
The GP was working at the Larksfield Surgery in Stotfold, near Hitchin, when the allegations were first made to police in 2013. He has been suspended.
He was released on bail on condition that he does not contact any of the complainants and must not seek employment as a GP.
